ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported
0= No problems at all; 1= Slight worries only; 2= Definite problems; 3= Very severe problems

ElementDescription: I have difficulties in getting and keeping close relationships.
Notes: 0= No problems at all; 1= Occasional problems; 2= Some problems; 3= Severe difficulties

ElementDescription: I feel lonely and isolated from other people.
Notes: 0= Not at all; 1= Not usually; 2= Much of the time; 3= Almost all the time
0= Not at all; 1= Not often; 2= Sometimes; 3= Very much

ElementDescription: I complete my tasks at work and home satisfactorily.
Notes: 0= Most of the time; 1= Quite often; 2= Sometimes; 3= Not at all

ElementDescription: I find my tasks at work and at home very stressful.
Notes: 0= Most of the time; 1= Quite often; 2= Sometimes; 3= Not at all

ElementDescription: I have problems in my sex life.
Notes: 0= No problems at all; 1= Occasional problems; 2= Moderate problems; 3= Severe problems

ElementDescription: I get on well with my family and other relatives.
